	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I'd say anything published by an established game company doesn't count as &quot;homebrew&quot;, since homebrew implies some sort of hobby project. It might be more misleading than helpful to introduce such rules, though.<br />Tengen releases definitely aren't &quot;homebrew&quot;, but you could make homebrew releases in the 80s and early 90s why not. I remember when the GBA was coming out and everyone was anxious to start creating homebrew for it right off the bat.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


