	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />It's hard to draw a line. But i agree that an element of hobbyism, for example in the form of bedroom coding, or &quot;one/a few people does it all&quot; is a criterium. <br />That doesn't necessarily exlude paid work, and definitely not exlude that there's work involved, paid or not. <br /><br />I think it's comparable to an independent musician/artist vs one employed or contracted by the music industry. <br /><br />We have <br />1)Independend artists (self managed; self released or coop released)<br />2)Independent labels (akin to retrotainment)<br />3)the industry (which presently is solely focusing on immaterial re-releases as far as NES software goes).

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
